post.summary:
The POST method allows the client to send accrual templates that will be imported by the Mediusflow master data import queue.
The accrual template have the company and the dimension values used in the template as prerequisites.

get.summary:
The GET method will allow you to check status for an imported batch. When performing a POST, the link returned is pointing to this mehtod.
This method allows the client to orchestrate so that the client can wait until dependent master data is imported correctly before sending that data.

parameters.name: importId
parameters.description: The import id is either retrieved byt he full link from the result of the POST or from within the XI master data import queue

delete.summary:
The DELETE mehtod allows a client to remove an import item from the queue, this to allow an integration to take full responsibility
of resending master data batches and handle all error on the client side instead of within Mediusflow. it's only possible to remove items that are not in a running state.

get.summary:
This method returns all messages that match the specified parameters.
The mandatory parameter is the status. All other parameters are sent as querystring parameters to narrow down the result.
The query string parameters are used, for example, to only return messages of certain type
The correlation key filter is used to filter out messages by the it's value, typically used to filter on invoice type or company.
The correlation key filter is built on a set of properties on the invoice with a delimiter: ';'.
(Be sure to check the number of ';' you have in your correlation key settings.)
For seeing all messages use ;;;;;; for a correlation key structure looking as: ERPId;company[49];supplier1;OrderItenfifier;CreatedDate;
To listen for a specific company, use a filter like: ERPID;company[49];;;;

parameters.name: messageStatus
parameters.description: Message statuses. these are: Posted, Fetched, Processing, Sent, Closed or Error

parameters.name: tag
parameters.description: Message tags. For a purchase order, these can be: REQUEST or CANCEL

parameters.name: correlationKeyFilter
parameters.description: The correlation key filter as explained in the summary

This method allows the client to orchestrate so that the client can wait until dependent master data is imported correctly before sending that data.

parameters.name: importId
parameters.description: The import id is either retrieved byt he full link from the result of the POST or from within the XI master data import queue

delete.summary:
The DELETE mehtod allows a client to remove an import item from the queue, this to allow an integration to take full responsibility
of resending master data batches and handle all error on the client side instead of within Mediusflow. it's only possible to remove items that are not in a running state.

parameters.name: importId
parameters.description: The import id is either retrieved by the full link from the result of the POST or from within the XI master data import queue

get.summary:
When calling this endpoint a list of suppliers will be returned.
There exists one filter parameter to this request, that is updatedSince, it filters out suppliers that have been changed since
the updatedSince time stamp.
It's possible adjust page sizes and offsets.

parameters.name: offset
parameters.description: The offset

parameters.name: limit
parameters.description: The number of records returned(max 1000)

parameters.name: updatedSince
parameters.description: Tells the service that we only want suppliers that have been changed after this date and time

post.summary:
The POST method allows the client to send suppliers that will be imported by the Mediusflow master data import queue.
The supplier have payment term and company as mandatory prerequisit.
If additional dimensions are going to be used or Vat groups they need to be imported in advance.

parameters.name: suppliers
parameters.description: The suppliers to import

201.description: Response includes Location header with a link to the import batch, this link will give the status of how the batch is processing within XI

get.summary:
The GET Method returns the status for a given DocumentImport document in Mediusflow.
It also returns the "real" invoice that was created by the imported document.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The id of the supplier invoice sent in. A full link to this method is returned by the POST method

post.summary:
The POST method imports a supplier invoice, this is done with multipart/form content.
The location header in the response includes a full link to the GET method, this link can be stored as a ticket/reciept that Mediusflow
recieved the imported document.
NOTE: Due to that it needs to be sent in as multipart/form, the self tested experience in Swagger UI is limited.
Please test this method and in the Postman tool, all examples can be found here: https://www.getpostman.com/collections/9d47658ed979b050b468

get.summary:
The GET method returns the supplier invoice content from a message that matches the status and the id.
If the message id is in another status, nothing will be returned. To find a message, use the other GET method that only provides message id as input.

parameters.name: messageStatus
parameters.description: The message status, can be Posted, Fetched, InProgress, Sent, Closed or Error

parameters.name: messageId
parameters.description: The id of the message

put.summary: This method updates the status for a supplier invoice message when processing it.

parameters.name: statusRequest
parameters.description: The status to set. Possible statuses Fetched and InProgress, Sent

parameters.name: messageId
parameters.description: The message id to change status for

parameters.name: messageStatus
parameters.description: The status that the message is in before the status change

get.summary:
The GET method with message id as input will return a status and an efective link to the real supplier invoice content.
The main idea with this method is to be ablet o check status for a give message and to be able to find where a message is interms of statuses.

parameters.name: messageId
parameters.description: The message id of the message to find/check status

get.summary:
This method returns all messages that matches the parameters sent in.
The mandatory parameter is the status parameter, besides that the other parameters are sent in as querystring parameters to narrow down the result.
The query string parameters are used to for instance limit on message type e.g. Preliminary or Posted.
The correalation key filter is used to filter out messages by the correlation key, typically used to filter on invoice type or by company.
The correlation key filter is built on a set of properties on the invoice with a delimiter: ';'.
(Please check the number of ';' you have in your correlation key settings.)
Seing all messages would be ;;;;;; for a correlation key looking as: company[49];company[49];supplier1;company[49];supplier1;Invoice1;
Listing for a given company would give the following filter: company[49];;;;;;

parameters.name: messageStatus
parameters.description: The message statuses, these are: Posted, Fetched, InProgress, Sent, Closed or Error

parameters.name: tag
parameters.description: The message tags, these can be the following for an invoice PRELIMINARY, FINAL or CANCEL

parameters.name: correlationKeyFilter
parameters.description: The Correlation key filter as explained in the summary

put.summary:
This method updates the status for all supplier invoice messages that meet the filter parameters.
This method behaves the same as the GET method that returns supplier invoice messages, please read there for details.

parameters.name: statusRequest
parameters.description: The status that you want to change

parameters.name: messageStatus
parameters.description: The message statuses, these are: Posted, Fetched, InProgress, Sent, Closed or Error

parameters.name: tag
parameters.description: The message tags, these can be the following for an invoice PRELIMINARY, FINAL or CANCEL

parameters.name: correlationKeyFilter
parameters.description: The Correlation key filter as explained in the summary

post.summary:
The POST method allows the client to send tax groups that will be imported by the Mediusflow master data import queue.
The tax group have company as mandatory prerequisit.
The tax group consists of a set of tax codes, in many "less advance" systems the translation is that tax code is the same as the tax group entity in Mediusflow.
This means that if a tax code from the ERP i X, then tax group will be X and there will be one tax code line with X within the tax group.
When performing accounting on an invoice, the tax group is the one used. When providing a TaxIndicator on Supplier or dimensions, the Tax Group is the one to reference.
There is a property IndicatorNumber, this one decides if the TaxGroup is going to work with TaxIndicator 1 or 2.

parameters.name: taxGroups
parameters.description: The tax groups to import

201.description: Response includes Location header with a link to the import batch, this link will give the status of how the batch is processing within XI

post.summary:
The POST method allows the client to send units that will be imported by the Mediusflow master data import queue.
The units have no prerequisit.
Remember that the functionality around units is limited in Mediusflow and the reason for importing them should probably be considered
before doing it. The usual case is to set the Unit on purchase order line to the default unit in Mediusflow => '-'

parameters.name: unit
parameters.description: The units to import

201.description: Response includes Location header with a link to the import batch, this link will give the status of how the batch is processing within XI

post.summary:
The POST method allows the client to send user configurations that will be imported by the Mediusflow master data import queue.
The user configurations have the company and the corresponding user as prerequisites.
Remember that by sending configurations for users the integration will updated them all the time, so manual changes of the properties included
in this data is not possible to set within Mediusflow.

parameters.name: userConfigurations
parameters.description: The user configurations to import

201.description: Response includes Location header with a link to the import batch, this link will give the status of how the batch is processing within XI
